This after reports were received that the Klein Olifants River is flooding a low-water bridge on the N11 making it impossible for vehicles to cross.
It is currently unclear what the status of the Hendrina-Arnot road is. Reports of a car that has been flushed away near Breyten was received. It can be confirmed from a trusted source that the driver of the car was washed ashore and was tended to by paramedics. Motorists are warned not to try and cross overflowing low-water bridges and to be wary of floods that might occur at any time. 